        "cooked": "<p>I know that there used to be some restrictions on file types, but now Signal can send pretty much any files. However, when I try to send a TIFF file as it is, with the .tif filename extension, Signal fails to do it (it shows ‚ÄúProcessing‚Ä¶‚Äù, then ‚ÄúRetry‚Äù).<br>\nIf I rename my SomeFile.tif to SomeFile.test, Signal sends it successfully.<br>\nI know that Chrome does not render TIFF files, and because of that, they cannon be properly treated as images. However, I would like to be able to simply send that .tif file as some unknown file type, like I did it after I renamed it to .test. I have not found anything useful to that end in Signal settings, nor in Android general settings. Am I missing somethng, is it possible to do it somehow, or shoud I submit a feature request etc.?</p>",
