        "cooked": "<aside class=\"quote group-volunteer_moderators\" data-username=\"Herohtar\" data-post=\"2\" data-topic=\"66011\">\n<div class=\"title\">\n<div class=\"quote-controls\"></div>\n<img loading=\"lazy\" alt=\"\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" src=\"https://community.signalusers.org/user_avatar/community.signalusers.org/herohtar/48/43780_2.png\" class=\"avatar\"> Herohtar:</div>\n<blockquote>\n<p>The workaround used to be sending it as a file attachment instead of as an image attachment.</p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>This is the first thing that would come to my mind. The problem is, I tried to send it as a file attachment, and Signal still seems to try to treat it as an image. Maybe it is about having it as some registered MIME type etc. When I see a list of files from which I try to select an attachment, it looks like this:<br>\n‚ÄúSomeFile.tif<br>\n10:51, 6.51 MB, TIFF image<br>\nSomeOtherFile.jpg<br>\nJan 9, 1.23 MB, JPG image<br>\nYetAnotherFile.PDF<br>\nDec 30, 2.34 MB, PDF document‚Äù<br>\netc. For the JPG file, there is a preview to the left of the file info. For TIFF (as well as for PDF) there is no preview, but it is still mentioned as an image, as I quoted above.</p>",
